{
  "texts": [
    "At a basic level, software is a set of instructions executed by a computer processor.",
    "Together, the software and the computer form a system.",
    "In the past, systems were often designed to handle a single type of data, either text or images represented as numbers and served specific purposes.",
    "Advanced single-purpose systems had complex instructions (algorithms), enabling them to perform tasks like playing chess.",
    "Systems designed to work with multiple types of data have increased capabilities but remain limited by their algorithms."
  ]
}